                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Love Video Game Developer Commentaries, These Are My Favorites]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-love-video-game-developer-commentaries-these-are-my-favorites/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Maximilian Padilla-Rodriguez]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/developer-commentary.jpg" length="1500" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[BioShock Remastered]]></category><category><![CDATA[Monkey Island 2: LeChuck's Revenge]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deus Ex: Human Revolution Director's Cut]]></category><category><![CDATA[Ghost of Tsushima Director's Cut]]></category><category><![CDATA[games]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There's a story behind every work of art, but these games let you hear it straight from the creators.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>For most games, the stories behind their development are a lot more complicated than you can believe. While most of these stories are only ever discussed behind closed doors, some games unveil their behind-the-scenes secrets through developer commentary.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 17:31:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-love-video-game-developer-commentaries-these-are-my-favorites/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8 Linux User Management Tricks With the usermod Command]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-user-management-tricks-with-the-usermod-command/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Zunaid Ali]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tux-the-linux-mascot-using-a-laptop-in-front-of-cinnamon-desktop-mountains-logo.png" length="1064" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Manage users like a pro.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The usermod command is a tool for updating details about an existing user account in your system. It's kind of like editing the "profile" of a Linux user. With it, you can adjust anything from the username to the login shell, without needing to delete and recreate the account.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-user-management-tricks-with-the-usermod-command/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Top 10 Websites That Defined the Early 2000s Internet]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/top-websites-that-defined-the-early-2000s-internet/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/retro-style-illustration-of-a-2000s-website-with-a-search-bar-digital-2000s-text-and-logos-of-neopets-newgrounds-xanga-and-yahoo-alongside-vintage-web-ads-and-a-pixelated-cursor.png" length="1183" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tech Throwback]]></category><category><![CDATA[internet]]></category><category><![CDATA[Internet Explorer]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The best sites from the Golden Era of the internet.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Back in the time of dial-up internet, the web was a far more colorful and chaotic place. Instead of spending most of our time on a handful of websites like we do now, web surfing was a real and fun activity.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/top-websites-that-defined-the-early-2000s-internet/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Windows Battery Settings That Actually Extended My Laptop’s Battery Life]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/change-windows-battery-settings/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/person-using-a-laptop-with-a-low-battery-icon-and-an-alert.jpg" length="738" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Charge less, do more!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Sick of your laptop battery running out in no time? It’s frustrating—especially when you can’t stay near a power outlet. I used to struggle with this too, but a few tweaks helped my laptop last longer on a single charge. Here are some tweaks you can make to save energy and stay unplugged for longer.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 16:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/change-windows-battery-settings/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[What Is Gaming Mode on a Motherboard, and Should You Enable It?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/my-motherboard-has-a-gaming-mode-heres-why-ive-disabled-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/final.jpg" length="338" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[AMD]]></category><category><![CDATA[CPUs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Gaming PCs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Confusingly, all Game Mode does is reduce performance.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you've recently built or bought an AMD-powered gaming PC and explored its BIOS, you might have noticed an option called "Gaming Mode," "Turbo Mode," or similar. However, this feature isn’t a simple performance boost you'd expect given its name. Here's what it actually does.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/my-motherboard-has-a-gaming-mode-heres-why-ive-disabled-it/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why I’ve Stuck With the MX Master Mouse for Over A Decade]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-ive-stuck-with-the-mx-master-mouse-for-over-a-decade/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/dygma-raise-keyboard-1.jpg" length="1130" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[Logitech MX Master 3S]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Desk]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            If it ain't broke, don't fix it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Have you ever just found a mouse that you fell in love with? Nearly a decade ago, I discovered the Logitech MX Master. Even though I’ve tried to replace it throughout the years, I keep coming back to it.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 15:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-ive-stuck-with-the-mx-master-mouse-for-over-a-decade/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Things Linux Has Taught Me About Open Source]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/things-linux-has-taught-me-about-open-source/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Graeme Peacock]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/tux-the-linux-penguin-mascot-holding-a-purple-open-source-logo-inside-a-screenshot-selection-frame-surrounded-by-icons-of-various-open-source-screenshot-tools.png" length="1740" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's important to understand and protect it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When you think of open-source software, you probably think of the cost (free), but that's not the full story. There's an entire ecosystem of both selflessness, selfishness, and moral ideals that make it up. I've outlined four things that using Linux has taught me about free and open-source software.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 15:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/things-linux-has-taught-me-about-open-source/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Most Reliable American SUV Comes With a Big Asterisk]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/most-reliable-american-suv-comes-with-big-asterisk/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-chevrolet-suburban-high-country-003.jpg" length="219" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This American SUV is super reliable, and tons hit crazy mileage for reasons beyond just tough build.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When it comes to <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/tag/suvs/" target="_blank">SUVs</a>, the real test isn’t the flashy features—it’s how long they’ll keep running. Reliability and the ability to just get the job done are what matter most.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 15:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/most-reliable-american-suv-comes-with-big-asterisk/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why Hack-and-Slash Is the Most Nonsense Gaming Genre]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-hack-and-slash-is-the-most-nonsense-gaming-genre/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Maximilian Padilla-Rodriguez]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/hack-and-slash-games.jpg" length="2092" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[tabletop]]></category><category><![CDATA[Retro Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            What does "hack-and-slash" mean to you?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When you think of hack-and-slash games, what's the first thing that comes to mind? Is it isometric RPGs like <em>Diablo</em>, stylish action games like <em>Devil May Cry</em>, or maybe even old-school table-top games like <em>Dungeons & Dragons</em>? Somehow, the genre encompasses all of these games and more, with very little in common.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 14:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-hack-and-slash-is-the-most-nonsense-gaming-genre/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Finally Found the Best Android Weather Widget]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-finally-found-the-best-android-weather-widget/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/android-weather-widgets-1.jpg" length="660" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This widget is simple, customizable, and elegant all at the same time. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Over the years, and more so recently, I've tried more Android weather apps and widgets than I care to admit. After my favorite app was no longer supported, I spent months looking for a replacement and have finally found the perfect weather widget for Android. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 14:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-finally-found-the-best-android-weather-widget/</guid></item></channel>
